    n, x = map(int, stdin.split())
    x = list(map(int, x.split()))
    min_count = max_count = 0

        min_count += min(3, len(set([x[i] - 1, x[i], x[i] + 1])))
        max_count += max(3, len(set([x[i] - 1, x[i], x[i] + 1])))
    
    return f"{min_count} {max_count}"

3. If the current bit is '1', increment the `count` variable and clear the bit using bitwise AND operator (&).
